# Python source conventions

## Style

- Line length 120, 4-space indent, double quotes (black/ruff)
- `from __future__ import annotations` in new modules
- NumPy docstrings; isort single-line imports; 2 blank lines after imports
- `snake_case` functions, `PascalCase` classes, `ALL_CAPS` constants, `_` private helpers

## Module boundaries

| Module | Edit when changing |
|--------|-------------------|
| `core.py` | Model registry, cost sorting, getters, fallbacks |
| `config.py` | Providers, import-time model enrichment |
| `filter_litellm.py` | `filter_models()`, priority order lists |
| `quality.py` | Quality scoring heuristic |
| `generate_configs.py` | Committed `configs/` artifacts |
| `__main__.py` | Tkinter GUI |

Re-export new public symbols from `__init__.py` and `__all__`.

## Patterns in this codebase

- Dataclasses for provider config
- Module-level singletons computed at import (`ALL_MODELS`, priority lists)
- `TYPE_CHECKING` blocks for heavy types; permissive mypy — match existing style
- Re-import guards: `if "VAR" not in globals():`
